HEADWORD: Diffusate
<hw>Dif*fus"ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Material which, in the process of catalysis, has diffused or passed
through the separating membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

